{
  "texts": [
    "Commentators and stakeholders have thus called for responsible digital health innovation.",
    "Responsible digital health innovation has been defined as \"any intentional systematic effort designed to increase the likelihood of a digital health technology developed through ethical decision making, being socially responsible and aligned with the values and well-being of those impacted by it\" 2, 5.",
    "International organizations and multinational companies have put forward and committed to a plethora of principles and guidelines for innovative approaches in digital health and AI 6.",
    "However, the adoption of responsible digital health principles in practice lags far behind their almost universal acceptance 2, 3, 7.",
    "Several impediments stand in the way of efficient and responsible digital health innovation."
  ]
}